<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-04-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-04-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="842" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d842">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">817.48 Earthquake of 1931/40</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The President of Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Moncada</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to President <persName type="to">Hoover</persName></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Translation]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-04-01">April 1, 1931</date>.<note n="8" xml:id="d842fn8">Received in the Department from the White House
                                    on April 2.</note></dateline></opener>
                        <p>I am profoundly thankful for the marks of the sympathy and the regret
                            which Your Excellency feels because of the Managua catastrophe, and in
                            the name of the Nicaraguan public and in that of my <pb facs="0908" n="788" xml:id="pg_788"/> Government I send to the people of the
                            United States and to Your Excellency my expressions of gratitude.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">J. M. Moncada</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>